BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:321@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260429
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260430
SUMMARY:BWA Y3: Mini London Marathon in Schools Event
DESCRIPTION:Mini marathon event for pupils in Years 3, 4, and 5.\n\nPupils from Year 3 (including 3B), Year 4 and Year 5 will be participating in the TCS Mini London Marathon. Children may choose between a competitive run of 7 laps or a 4-lap fun run. Parents and carers are invited to attend and watch the competitive run, and are welcome to join the fun run. Please ensure children wear PE kits, bring a water bottle, and have sun cream/hats if needed. Parents will be collected from the gate at 8:50am.
CATEGORIES:SPORTS
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:322@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260421
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260422
SUMMARY:BWA: Chelsea Physic Garden Outing (Y1B)
DESCRIPTION:School trip for Y1B class to Chelsea Physic Garden for a 'Plant Hunters' workshop.\n\nThe GSB (Y1B) class will visit Chelsea Physic Garden to conclude their plant project. Pupils will attend a 'Plant Hunters' workshop and explore the garden. Lunch will be eaten on-site. For pupils enrolled at BWA, the cost is £5.18. Five parent volunteers are requested to accompany the class.
CATEGORIES:TRIP
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:323@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260424
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260425
SUMMARY:BWA: Professional Bike Health Checks
DESCRIPTION:Professional bike health checks available at school as part of Earth Week 2026.\n\nAs part of Earth Week 2026 celebrations, the PTA is joining the APL to host a professional Bike Health Check service at the school. Pricing: 10 GBP for a small bike, 14 GBP for a big bike (24 inches and above). Advance booking is required via the school events portal. Drop off bikes between 8:00 AM and 9:00 AM in front of the school; pick up at the end of the school day from inside the school grounds.
CATEGORIES:COMMUNITY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:324@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260423
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260424
SUMMARY:BWA: Deadline -  Notification of student departure for September
DESCRIPTION:Request for parents to inform the school office if their child will not be returning to BWA in September.\n\nMiss Henry, Headteacher, requests that parents inform the school office in writing if their child will not be returning to Belleville Wix Academy in September to assist with planning and class organization. If no notification is received, the school will assume the child is returning.
CATEGORIES:ADMIN
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR